Be yourself love !

To be PRESENT. I owed myself a birthday detached from my phone as much as possible. 

This whole week leading up to Dom Day as Prime video called it (🥹)was nothing short of epic. 

SWARM premiered to so much love and praise …beyond what I could’ve hoped for.

 I came home to Brooklyn and spend my birthday with Angela Yee ( out today 1pm et) and Z100( available now)

After that I went to Wyckoff Gardens Center in Brooklyn to speak to some kids. To be able to go there on my birthday felt more like purpose being fulfilled than a celebration of me. I didn’t not expect anything still they bought me cake and roses and sing Happy Birthday to me and counted up to 32 😳😂…Then I saw my mom and sister. 

 I came to my hotel with so many flowers waiting for me. I had FaceTime, calls and was showered with love. Thank you guys 🥹😍🥹

For me though- 

 I launched my own collection of #BeYourselfLove hats and hoodie that you can buy at the link in bio. 🚀🚀🚀

More reflection to come

“If a writer falls in love with you, you can never die” - I don’t know who but still I know this to be true ✍🏽

When a show is invited to @deadline contenders panel it is “for your consideration…” (awards and things….) I’ve seen these words most of my life. I’ve  put them on vision boards in hopes of one day manifesting a role that would show just how much I could do if given the chance and those words would hopefully follow at the end. 

In this season of loving, celebrating and radically unearthing my own Black womanhood and the unprecedented opportunity to bring a character like Dre to life.  @whatisjoedoing “Black like you”particularly hits a sweet chord within me. 

A Black woman chameleon of a character who allowed me the chance to be multiple versions of her each episode.  Gifted me the shot to dance in the world of physical comedy similar to the kind that first inspired me as a kid, to explore a rage so guttural and raw. To love deep, to waltz with wounded feminine and masculine energies, to get to do it on your tv screens unapologetically , to star and PRODUCE and to come out lighter than I was before. 

For it to premiere to world and be doused in so much LOVE there couldn’t be a more perfect song.  At the swarm premiere Joe asked me “who’s your favorite artist?” I immediately responded … “you.” To watch him create music has inspired me for a lifetime. And he just doesn’t disappoint. 

Congratulations! What an anthem. #Blacklikeyou 🥹 with that voice and his pen he created a beautiful love song to black women and it dropped today so go pour yourself some now …

Though I encourage you to sip it slowly and savor every second because its hot 🥵. 

Then have some more and see him on tour in may!

BE YOURSELF, LOVE.

A line that I developed based off of one of the most simple yet profound things someone ever said to me….

Spent the last 3 years unpacking every layer and piece of what that concept could mean fully.
 
I deeply appreciate the journalists, writers, editors and the outlets who have pushed beautiful clips of me being myself and being love.

 Very generous comments from so many.. I’m glad I am in a place to receive the love and know I am worthy ;) - swipe to understand 

1. “God’s promise fulfilled “

2. “I am worth it.  I have breath in my body I’m worth it “

3. Love for myself can’t be transactional either

4. ASL - this clip has inspired people to learn ASL and also reminded me of my love for the Language and  to practice my signing again. You have to sign slow with me. I’m not a master signer. I just put myself out there to learn. So much love to actual interpreters and teachers. You are magic and I hope to one day get there. 🫶🏽

“Of the Essence”

I love WORDS. And “ESSENCE” is just one of those words. 

I remember in the beginning of my tv/film career fighting against the idea of stereotypes by rejecting the idea of a character before looking at the soul of their story and what it might do for mine. 

I was only able to get out of my own way when I realize I did in fact love the essence of the character anyways and so I decided I did not have to play into the label but instead uphold the ESSENCE OF THEIR CHARACTER.

Definition
:the intrinsic nature or indispensable quality of something, especially something abstract, that determines its character.

the most significant element, quality, or aspect of a thing or person

of the essence
: of the utmost importance

Thank you @essence for this digital cover, such a beautiful article and declaring that I am of the utmost importance. So much love to y’all

#heroinewithathousandfaces #beyourselflove

SWARMING THOUGHTS:  The making of Character

I used to loved getting DVDS back in the day because of the bonus clips they shared where actors and creatives  would reflect on scenes from the movies that we loved.

I love talking about craft and how I came to understand my characters.

 DRE is such a deeply complex character and I learned so much from playing her that I had this idea of some kind of actors series called swarming thoughts: the making of character. 

Anyway I decided to try it out here with one of my favorite acting moments in #swarm with the phenomenal @kiersey. 

More reflections to come 🐝🤓🐝

Let me know your swarming thoughts 🐝🐝🐝
#swarmingthoughts #heroinewithathousandfaces

SWARMING THOUGHTS: The Making of Character

I decided not to put the making of “A” character because I do believe that because I always extend myself so much to the roles I take, I started setting the intention of using their life experiences as  opportunity to grow as person and evolve my own internal sense of character.

These characters make me as much as I make them. I say that I got freeDOM and healing at Dre’s expenses. She navigates a rage that I never have to know. Sometimes our characters do things so that we don’t have to.

I love this scene. @chloebailey acting is so beautiful in it. 

With the Rashida scene it required a really strong actress to deliver a monologue like that because Dre needs to be so stunned she can’t  respond. 

@kiersey is a gift of an actress. We really lucked out.

In this one Dre has to make tactical choices physically and vocally to get what she wants. Playing off of the gentle sincerity and pleading from Chloe’s marissa makes this a really heart wrenching break up. 

It couldve been so easy for someone to come in and play Marissa in a way that also bullies and ostracizes Dre but Chloe is so sweet and talented she makes Marissa a character that gives Dre and the audience so much to hold on to for the rest of season. 

In acting class you learn to consider how the character is different from the beginning of a scene to the end or the beginning of a series to the end. It really was an honor to play so many characters in one.
#swarmingthoughts #heroinewithathousandfaces #swarmonprime
@essence  check out the full video on Essence.com but I wanted to give a special shout out to Brooklyn today!!!

SWARMING THOUGHTS: The making of character
😂😅 
Episode 102 directed by @adamma.ebo 
Really I tried to do all the things @nicolethepole and  @misschromediva told me NOT to do. 

It’s not sexy to lay flat like a fish and it is disgraceful not to POINT THOSE TOES.
Dark night was on set with me and choreographed both dances.

Even though it was only two scenes I first started learning pole dancing with Nicole in La. I had about 5 sessions.  I paid for pole lessons and a pole in the crib because I think it’s better to know the rules and break them then to go with no knowledge of it at all. Plus everything was shot on film so it would be really expensive to do a lot of takes.

I talk a lot about masculine and feminine energy and the internal exploration of having both inside us all.  Dre really allowed me to navigate both energies and that was amazing.

Sidebar:
The floor was extremely waxy . I was not at an advantage but I’m a child of the most high and so he got us through it 😅😂

I told you guys I give every year a word right?

2019- spirit year and I got a good dose of the magic of the ancestors

2020- freeDOM year and I had an awakening that taught me the power of God’s universe and our own sovereign universe inside of us all, which is the mind. That’s where freeDom comes from 

2021- surrender year- be careful what you ask for because I was forced to surrender. There was no more space in me for the old paradigms to exist.

2022 - flow year- I learned that most of my our suffering comes from resistance to what is and I wanted to learn how to be like water.

2023- light year- to be light about the things that always made me feel so heavy.

Within my light year there are subtitles 
1-6- stratosphere season
7-12 - ethereal season

Let’s watch it unfold.
#glorytogod #beyourselflove

Last night I wrote- Y’all I legit have tears in my eyes putting this together. F***king TLC yooooo. @therealchilli @therealtboz @officialtlc 

I didn’t even have the words to express to them how much they mean and meant to me and I still don’t . I just kept saying “you don’t even know…. 🙄😅😩”

No words will suffice. 
No rhyme would be dope enough
 to encompass the way my heart beats faster 
with nostalgia 
when I hear waterfalls.
Or how my arms and knees automatically sway 
when creep creeps in from the DJ 
or how me and cousins had no business singing red light special and diggin on you, but we did and then performed it for our parents 😅 with tied up shirts 
singing with all our heart into some tv remotes 
pretending to be YOU.

The outfits, the hairstyles and the RAW ATTITUDE. I remember watching documentaries and being like wow they talk like me, they got fire in their speech and ain’t nothing wrong with that. I love you women!

I can go on and on but I’m really emotional sitting on my couch in La so far from home and my family but it’s because God called me to do big things and live a big life, filled with big dreams.
And the fact that they were talking about me and my talent and work??? Wow 🥹🤯 

I’m incredibly humbled. This night I’ll never forget. Shout out to @nicolethepole for being there and genuinely supporting my joy.

SWARMING THOUGHTS: The making of character  ep 105

I want to talk about the technical arc of this monologue. The idea of starting in one place as a character and ending up somewhere different. This scene was fun because Dre wears all her emotions on sleeve. Earlier in this interaction she’s pissed that Erica has a tattoo of Marissa face. She can’t kill her in this public place so she decides the next best thing is to destroy her sense of reality. Toy with her mind. But she ends  believing it herself.😳

Acting in Film and TV by Michael Caine first made me realize how much what you choose to look at and when affects the audience. Joseph Hacker talked about having an opinion about the people you speak of when your character says names. I journal because I want to create that reality in my mind. I don’t go to set thinking about what I wrote I just trust that now it’s in my subconscious.

Also to clarify why I didn’t know the monologue was filming  that day

-I’m so thankful to have been able to stretch and challenge myself to this extent. To know what Im really made of 💪🏾. There’s no B storyline, this means that everyday the crew was there filming, meant I had to be there too. No real break. Even the weekends required that i was doing something for the role. The schedule was definitely very intense and demanding but the result is worth it 🥹! 

The amount of people that have enjoyed the work is an honor… and to nerd out on here over scenes with you guys is a gift that this hard work has given me.

So I wrapped on set the night before and didn’t have the emotional or mental capacity to review lines or what was filming the next day which is not me at all. When I woke up to practice dialect coaching with @audreylecrone I was SHOOK! That monologue is like 5 minutes long. We were shooting on film ( which really means you can’t waste a take) but we didn’t panic 

… I accepted the fact that I’m human. I can only do what I can do… my best. Also reminded myself “it’s acting it’s not life or death, Dom, You don’t have to be perfect you just have to be. “ 

So here to being.

#swarmingthoughts #heroinewithathousandfaces #beyourselflove #glorybetogod

SWARMING THOUGHTS : The making of Character.

I do believe that we can channel when we act. This day when I left set I was physically in pain . I couldn’t keep my eyes open, slurring all my words. I felt as though my spirit was fighting something all day and I was finally able to rest.

I really did give everything I had to Dre. I got freeDOM  at her expense. 
 
Special shout out to our director @adamma.ebo she was a saving grace for me.

I remember she didnt want me to do it too many times but they caught a new angle so I gave them one more take and that take is included when Dre/Tony looks away from Rashida 

Special thanks to her, our DP drew and the editors.
#swarmingthoughts #heroinewithathousandfaces

🌻Coach me baby 🌻

DOMINIQUE X COACH

Thanking y’all for giving me my flowers… both literally and figuratively 🥹🥹🥹

Moved , humbled, honoured, excited, inspired..

Balancing one of the biggest accomplishments of my career with one of the most necessary movements in our industry is interesting for sure but what I’ve come to learn is that multiple things can be true at once and so can a plethora of feelings about those things and it’s our job to make room to tend to all those things within ourselves .

I decided that if we have one life to live…I want to spend it exploring the deepest crevices of my soul and then expressing what I’ve found there, in any art form my soul so chooses. - @dometcetera 

Song cry 2021 was my first try. 

I’ve been in the studio lately too. A real dream come true! In fact, I create my own original song…. Vocals, Lyrics, melody, chord progression, played the Keys, did background vocals and harmonies with help from beautiful friends and mind blowing artists. Can’t wait to share more.

Now in 2023 God has continued to surround me with musicians that I admire…

I think for a while I forgot how to smile. 

Repression is such a dimmer of the divine light we all have inside of us and it is so stealthy. 

I somehow let experiences and pain put a filter on me, of which I could not see. 
That’s ok. We live to learn 🫶🏽

One day in June last summer, I randomly walked into a wholistic shop in Brooklyn. 

I said something to my friend and it was in there that the owner,  a black woman, told me that “I had resisted too long.”
I wanted to catch an attitude cause nobody asked her 😂 but I couldn’t because I knew she was right  and I did in fact walk in that shop hopeful for insight. 🧘🏾‍♀️

She said we have “3 choices in life.. Ignore. Resist or follow… “ could it be that all these years I confused resisting and  following …

I thought that by verbalizing I didn’t agree with something that was resistance but in fact was I still just following? 
 
Now I know, it was that I was resisting the wrong thing. I was resisting my own heart. 

Why do we do such hurtful things like that?

This January I declared that I just wanted to wake up everyday and be happy not because of what’s happening in my career or my love life but just of my own volition. 

 So happy to see I’m smiling again and this time it’s a smile of my own making  and still I appreciate you guys for holding space for it. 🥹☺️🌀🪷🦋✨
